manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Why choose our USB Type C Male to Female Adapter? This Type-C extender protects your Type C port from wear and tear while keeping your case intact.This 100W USB C adapter with LED power display shows the fast charging power in real time, featuring a visual design that lets you know the current charging speed and monitor the status of your device in real time. The USB C adapter supports PD3.0/QC3.0/PPS and other fast charging protocols, and can realize a maximum 20V/5A, 100W USB power output to provide the fastest charging speed for your devices, with a data transfer speed of up to 480 Mbps. High quality zinc alloy shell is durable and ultra-compact design is easy to carry or store, exquisite exterior details and strict quality testing standards, USB C male and USB C female USB C adapters have passed 10,000+ push and pull tests. USB-C adapter is easy to use, no driver or software required, plug and play.

Easy to connect USB-C peripherals Long enough and compact enough to make connection easy when your device case gets in the way of any external accessories. No need to remove the case when connecting! Extremely simple design This zinc alloy cased USB Type C expansion adapter is one of the most compact options on the market. The ultra-compact design is easy to carry or store. Make life easier Supports charging and data synchronization. It also reduces wear and tear on your device's USB-C ports, so you can simply tape it to the ends of your device and not have to worry about losing the adapter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cool little "chicklet" to see how your device is grabbing power
reviews.reviewText: Interesting to know how my device is pulling power, how much, and what protocol. They are small and easily connect to my cable and the device.To the manufacturer... on my laptop with the USB-C port on the left side, the display is reversed. It would be a great upgrade to this to somehow flipping the display around for left hand connections. Also, the display could be a smidge brighter but it is otherwise very readable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars If all you need is a rough idea of USB-C power on the wire, this is a good bargain
reviews.reviewText: Pros:1) Very inexpensive2) 2-pack allows simultaneous monitoring of two USB-C cables3) Appears to be accurateCons:1) Display is constantly changing. I'd prefer that it report out average power over some period like 1 or 2 seconds rather than what appears to be instantaneous changes2) Display is relatively dim compared to real USB-C power meters or a USB-C cable with builtin display3) While power can flow throw this product, when I tried to use it in an application where power and data were flowing, it didn't work for me.Overall: it really depends on what one is looking for. This is NOT a full-function USB-C power meter, but it might be a great bargain for some who have lower expectations.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love using this device so I can know for sure the devices I charge is adequately being charged. It's not enough to see the device taking a charge, as much as knowing exactly what the charge rate is. I need to know to be able to figure out if I have a defective charger or cord and it saves the charging port from excessive wear and tear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this to confirm charging power & speed
reviews.reviewText: These are amazing. USB-C has introduced both simplicity and complexity to charging cables. I use these to confirm charging speed on airplanes (from the screen and from the power outlet -- VERY different). The number lights up and you can quickly glance at it to confirm your phone is still charging, for example from a loose outlet where your charger brick might loosen and stop charging. Love this on airplanes, love this at airports, love while travelling, love in hotel rooms, love when using travel adapters, love when using charging pads. I also use this to confirm which cables are slow-charging. I've purchased probably 10 of these so far and give them to my family. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewText: They seem to do exactly what they purport to do. Quick and easy to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Fell apart the first time I plugged it in.
reviews.reviewText: This is a simple review. The first time I plugged it in the shell of the device slid forward. When the shell slid forward the lens fell out. So be careful plugging in the device else it will fall apart. The better idea is to find another option and pass on this product.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Meh one worked one really didn’t.
reviews.reviewText: So I have one working ok and another one doesn’t work. Very strange. Maybe I got one bad unit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: While being able to keep an eye on the amount of power going to the device and whether or not you are utalizing PD (Power Delivery where supported) it is connected to, you can definetly know when the charge is complete. With this it can add the feature to know how much is going into the device with standard cables. However, one thing I have come to find, the display does not stay on when power draw is about 2W (Watts) or under which would be ideal when connected to a power bank, but when connected to a wall charger, to me does not matter too much for which this will be used. Apart from that this is a nice option to have when using random cables I have lying around the house and still want to see the amount of power used.
